## Beringia Marine — Project Rules

### Architecture
- **Monorepo**: pnpm workspaces + Turborepo. Apps in `apps/`, shared packages in `packages/`.
- **Active web surface**: `apps/web` is the production Next.js app. Do not add new web code at the repo root.
- **CMS**: Sanity Studio lives in `apps/studio`. Web-side Sanity runtime code is in `apps/web/src/sanity/`.
- **Shared config**: Site identity, shell navigation, and business defaults live in `packages/config`.

### Styling
- CSS Modules co-located with components. No Tailwind.
- BEM-inspired class naming within modules.
- Use CSS custom properties (`--depth-*`, `--color-*`, `--font-*`) for theming and depth-zone adaptation.
- Depth-driven variables are defined in `apps/web/src/app/globals.css` under `html[data-home-depth]` selectors.
- Transitions between depth zones use `--depth-transition` and `--depth-ease` for unified timing.

### Homepage Depth System
- Five oceanic zones: `epipelagic`, `mesopelagic`, `bathypelagic`, `abyssal`, `hadal`.
- Zone definitions in `apps/web/src/lib/depth-zones.ts`.
- `HomepageDepthObserver` sets `html[data-home-depth]` based on scroll position.
- `DepthBackground` (fixed, layered gradient) provides the environmental field.
- Header, cards, buttons, links, footer all inherit depth state via CSS variables.
- Hierarchy of adaptation: Environment > Header > Cards > Buttons/Links/Dividers > Metadata.

### Content
- Static marketing content in `apps/web/src/lib/content/beringia-static.ts`.
- Solutions registry in `apps/web/src/lib/content/solutions.ts`.
- Insights use a canonical registry consumed by both listing and detail routes.
- Prefer shared helpers for insight URLs and SEO image resolution.

### Code Conventions
- TypeScript throughout. Strict mode.
- Next.js App Router patterns: server components by default, `'use client'` only when needed.
- Keep components focused. Prefer composition over deep prop drilling.
- After edits, run lint/type checks scoped to changed areas. Avoid unrelated refactors.

### Content & Branding
- Remove legacy Vital Ice branding/assets when encountered; replace with Beringia usage.
- Package names still reference `@vital-ice/*` in some places — rename incrementally.
- Keep newsletter flow patterns intact unless explicitly asked to remove them.

### Documentation
- Active docs in `docs/`. Legacy template docs archived in `docs/archive/`.
- Planning documents archived in `docs/archive/planning/`.
- Prior migration reference in `migration-legacy/`.
